definition.value: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 43 with 7 double bonds.
A phenylethylamine having the phenyl substituent at the 2-position.

A maltodextrin in which the alpha-(1->4)-linked D-glucose units form a linear chain, typically from 3 to 17 glucose units long. (Cf. amylose, in which the chain length ranges from around 300 to several thousand glucose units).
